The paper deals with the interaction between network effects and economic incentives in P2P file sharing systems. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY), systems and control (cs.SY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on network effects and incentives, we believe that cs.SI and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CY, cs.SY, and cs.CR.
